  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[From Blogspot to Octopress/Github]]></title>
    <link href="http://claymore.github.com/blog/2012/11/04/from-blogspot-to-octopress-slash-github/"/>
    <updated>2012-11-04T21:53:00+04:00</updated>
    <id>http://claymore.github.com/blog/2012/11/04/from-blogspot-to-octopress-slash-github</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;ve finally moved my blog from Blogspot to Github pages. The blog is now powered by <a href="http://octopress.org/" title="Octopress">Octopress</a>. Blogspot was convient but for a developer there are several reasons to switch. Octopress generates a static website that can be deployed anywhere so you gain independence from a service provider. Your posts are Markdown files that can be authored in your favorite editor. The blog source is under version control. Another great feature: code syntax highlighting works out of the box.</p>
]]></content>
